main event: A civilian observed a UFO over Omaha, Nebraska for approximately 7 minutes on April 18, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting involved a single object that increased in brightness and appeared as a point of light through binoculars., The apparent size of the UFO was about 2/3 of what could be seen by the naked eye., The object was visible in scattered haze conditions and had self-luminosity., The witness noted that the object could not be seen with the naked eye at times, but remained visible through binoculars., The UFO moved east to west at a speed comparable to that of a television broadcast signal.
sighted object: a single self-luminous point of light
witness description: a civilian who used binoculars to observe the object
